  "Metadata" -> {
   "built" -> "{2026, 4, 12, 17, 59, 1.375575}", 
    "history" -> {"14.3", "", "", ""}, "context" -> "QuantumMob`Q3`", 
    "keywords" -> {
     "fermionic quantum computation", "fermionic Gaussian state"}, 
    "specialkeywords" -> {}, "tutorialcollectionlinks" -> {}, "index" -> True,
     "label" -> "Quantum Mob/ Q3 Symbol", "language" -> "en", "paclet" -> 
    "QuantumMob/Q3", "status" -> "None", "summary" -> 
    "WickState[u] represents a fermionic Gaussian pure state without pairing \
correlation. The particles in the state occupy the dressed modes \
characterized by the isometric rectangular matrix u. WickState[{0, n}] \
represents the vacuum state of the Fock space for n fermion modes. \
WickState[{Null, n}] represents the null state of the Fock space for n \
fermion modes. WickState[{n1, n2, ...}, n] returns a WickSate object \
corresponding to the computational basis state Ket[{n1, n2, ...}] of m \
fermion modes. If the list of occupation numbers {n1, n2, ...} is shorter (or \
longer) than m, then the occupation numbers are cyclically repeated (or the \
list is simply cut).", "synonyms" -> {}, "tabletags" -> {}, "title" -> 
    "WickState", "titlemodifier" -> "", "metadescription" -> "", 
    "windowtitle" -> "WickState", "type" -> "Symbol", "uri" -> 
    "QuantumMob/Q3/ref/WickState"}},
